# Comments & Documentation

Comments explain **why** and **invariants** — not narration. Match the dense voice in existing playback, provider, and database files.

## When to comment

| Situation | Example |
|-----------|---------|
| MPV property ordering | `// 'start' must be set before loadfile — mpv race on Android #226` |
| Provider coalescing | `// Coalesces concurrent loadLibraries() — sidebar + screen share provider` |
| Drift migration | `// schemaVersion 16 — FK cascades re-enabled in beforeOpen after migration` |
| Stable enum ids | `// Stable string id — .name would corrupt existing OfflineWatchProgress rows` |
| Platform branch | `// ExoPlayer default on Android — MPV fallback when user disables in settings` |
| Sync / watch state | `// Offline queue drains on reconnect — server wins on conflict per SyncRules` |

## Tags

```
// TODO(emby): <action> — <reason>
// Plezy-legacy: <note> — when touching code pending Emby-only simplification
```

## Public APIs

- Doc comments on `abstract interface class`, sealed types, and non-obvious service methods.
- `packages/emby_core` — document repository contracts and Emby API assumptions.

## README / CONTRIBUTING

Update when adding: new env vars for integration tests, codegen steps, platform setup, or emby_core smoke workflow.

## Forbidden

- Narration (`// increment counter`, `// call API`)
- Commented-out dead code left behind
- Docs that contradict `scripts/ci_checks.sh` or `CONTRIBUTING.md`
